links.title: CVS Health raises 2020 earnings guidance as plan to offer wide range of medical services pays off
links.description: CVS Health reported a better-than-expected 3.5% jump in third-quarter revenue and raised its 2020 earnings guidance on Friday as its plan to remake the drugstore chain into a health service company paid off. Offering everything from insurance to Covid-19 testing, the health-care company also named a new CEO.
